HEADWORD: Apician
<hw>A*pi"cian</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Apicianus</ets>.]</ety> <def>Belonging to Apicius, a notorious
Roman epicure; hence applied to whatever is peculiarly refined or dainty
and expensive in cookery.</def> <rj><au>H. Rogers.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

